@Xavier 

Hello Xavier,

Do you think that some of the money spent on infrastructure also impacts families?  For example would increasing access to high-speed broadband or investing funds to improve transportation to underserved communities contribute in a meaningful way to the well being of families?

@DeAnthony Alston 
Welcome DeAnthony.

With respect to what you raised in (2), is there a benefit to families when we spend money on infrastructure?  How could we use historical data about such spending to make a hypothesis about what those benefits might be?

@Kz  Bax 

There are a lot of pieces to the infrastructure portion of this budget.  Do you think there are aspects of infrastructure spending that may also positively impact the families portion?  

I wonder what history says about the economic impact of other federal spending plans from previous administrations.

@Alfredo 

Hello fellow Tucsonan!

Do you think that the way we fund teacher pay might be a reason that the education section is the smallest portion of all?  It might be an interesting to investigate how those funds are derived and what would need to change so that federal spending on teachers would have more of an impact.

@Kristian 

Welcome fellow Tucsonan,

While low pay for educators is of concern to many, is it possible that the reason for this budget allocating such a small portion to teachers due to how we fund education in this country?  It might be a good idea to explore the sources of funding for education as a way to continue with what you noticed.

@Zoe 
Hello fellow citizen of The Old Pueblo!
Do you think that the fact that the infrastructure portion has so many subparts means that it will be easier to reduce proposed spending in infrastructure once negotiations with Congress begin?

@Ava 

Hello Ava,

I also wonder why in-home care is classified as infrastructure.  Do you think that this classification was made by the Biden administration?  If so, perhaps contactinghttps://www.whitehouse.gov/ could yield an answer as to why it was made so.

